review:
I've played this game since beta and release state and here is what i can say about Sea of Thieves.
Probably the most stisfying and immersive experience that you can get, however the game lacks on some content and mechanics seems a bit odd. The biggest advantage here is visual design. Although it looks like a game for minor audience but in reality it's not- game mechanics that are suited for more experienced players that are up for a challenge either it's pve or pvp persist withing everything that this game provides to a player. BUT! The biggest issues are still: 
-Repetative and long grind for pirate legend (3 vendors must be at reputation level 50); 
-Outposts are not safe zones that should be considered as mini hub island where you can sell your loot or browse vendors inventory without getting killed in process and loose everything you've spent your time on (i do understand that it is the main game feature, when you are out on your voyage in search for loot you put yourself on a high risk, but as you progress pvp players are getting annoying and really hard to get rid of and pirate legends seems unobtainable at this point for at least solo players which this game does not tolerate and reward for being brave and bold so to say);
-Occasional event-obstacles like skeleton ships are probably the most unfair due to the fact if you are a solo player you will have to do your best to sunk them, repair your ship and shoot back all at the same time, even though it is somewhat easier to encounter them as duo team they are still had to be sunk in order to get rid of them which is kind of different story against megalodon which does nothing if you don't shoot it and just mind your buisness and karaken which you can escape from relatively easy. 

Other then that: the gameplay, the story, overall quality and the amount of content (primarily- cosmetics) to pursue is just great. Really looking forward to see what this game will look like in the nearest future with new updates.

I'm here to tell anyone trying to decide if they want to buy this game or not my opinion and personal experience. Been playing since a few days before Official release through Microsoft over 2 years ago. Way more hours played than I want to admit. 

If you've NEVER played the game; 
Buy it. Live it. Love it. Some of the most fun I've had in a video game. The random unexpected chaos is amazing! It truly is about the adventure and fun. No regrets and I honestly can see myself still playing 10+ years from now. I have now purchased the game through Microsoft and Steam.

For those who own the Microsoft version; 
My FPS increased by 30 with the Steam version. Steam also gives me a fullscreen and I no longer lose my mouse. The Steam overlay is usable as well as the Discord Overlay. Steam also gives you a running "Hours Played" counter so you can see exactly how much of your life you're truly investing. :P You still invite your friends through Xbox. I have zero regrets spending an additional $40 just for those things alone.
